        "client_msg_id": "8620b989-c030-474d-a72f-680303f73af8",
        "text": "I think you have the direction wrong.  You can accept CRAN's hostkey.  As Inaki said:\n> With SSH (once you have saved CRAN's public key), even if you are redirected, the malicious server does not have CRAN's private key, so the connection won't be established in the first place.\nas the (public) key of CRAN stored on your machine is used to authenticate the private CRAN key only CRAN has.  CRAN is not in the business of dealing with (potentially millions of) keys by R users (or even mirror admins).  Given a server you trust (your local cache) you can read from it with R's functions or any of the add-on packages you like.",
        "team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "source_team": "T01DW9DLB2A",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "g4e96ca7ae02",
